name: Jewel Snob February 2010
description:
On Jewel Snob:
'While in NY for Fashion Week, I went to visit Paige Gamble's showroom. She is amazing, to put it plainly. Paige has an eye like no other, she is sharp witted, gorgeous, genius and most importantly (for our purposes) phonemically creative. I am in love with her bags, they are immaculate and chic, it's sick!! So when she started doing jewelry, you know I was all over it. Her pieces are like works of art, they are unique without being unwearable. The thing I love most is that you can wear a simple outfit with her pieces to spice things up and it is totally effortless but entirely put together. I am crazy over the Amethyst and Gunmetal Chains ($550) , it is a perfect mix of feminine and bold. In the summer, white tee, jeans and this and you are rocking like no other.'

Polished Faceted Amethyst Strands Hand-Woven with Gunmetal Chains. Ties with double-faced satin ribbon allowing the wearer to adjust the length to her liking. Hand-made in NYC. Due to the unique nature of the stones and technique, each necklace may vary slightly.

name: Conde Nast Traveler Word Of Mouth February 2010
description:
'In last May's WOM, we featured a crinkly python headband by globally inspired designer Paige Gamble. Now the New Yorker is doing necklaces, twisting Brazilian and Mexican agate, Peruvian pyrite and Indian garnets onto industrial metal chains. The splurge-worthy ($550 a piece!) baubles are available online and in Gamble's new Aspen store, where you can also buy her choice leather clutches and bags. '

Polished Faceted Teal Brazilian Agate Hand-Woven with Gunmetal Chains. Tied with chiffon ribbon allowing the wearer to adjust the length to her liking. Hand-made in NYC.

Polished Faceted Amethyst Strands Hand-Woven with Gunmetal Chains. Ties with double-faced satin ribbon allowing the wearer to adjust the length to her liking. Hand-made in NYC.

name: Bag Snob October 2009
description:
Bag Snob October 5th, 2009

As you can imagine, I have seen A LOT of bags. But I have never seen anything like this! Tattoo on ostrich!! Is that insanely brilliant or what? The hand-engraved and one of a kind tulip tattoo is set against matte vanilla ostrich for contrast and impact. This is not just drawn in, this is actually done like a tattoo where the ink is put into the skin. It is then brushed down to prevent rub off but you still get the buttery finish of the ostrich. It is elegance meets edgy done just right. Fabulousness at this level gives me the ultimate high, I love what I do so much!!! This "folio" is a large clutch and the best part is that it's big enough for work papers so you can be the coolest person in the office. It has a magnetic closure that is amazingly tight yet really easy to open. It measures 13.25" long x 8" tall. Each piece is custom made and requires 3-5 weeks to deliver, email Paige to order, $3400. Take a look at Paige Gamble's website.

name: Front Desk July/August 2009
description:
"Sometimes luxury goods are so special the only way to see them is to meet with the designers themselves.  So it is with Paige Gamble, who creates bags and clutches in exotic skins and sells them to private clients at her atelier on 64th Street.  While she focuses on using the best she can find in alligator, eel, ostrich, python and stingray skins, the greatest parts are in the details such as seriously cool add-ons like pyrite or amethyst clasps."

Burnished Python Empire Python Tote - Medium Each bag is cut from one continuing piece of large-scaled python Lined in burnished gold python and tan suede Two interior cell phone pockets, 1 large zippered pocket 15" long x 10" tall x 7" deep
